The paper discusses the recent advances in Cloud Radio Access Networks (C-RANs), which is a topic related to networking and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses key techniques such as fronthaul compression, large-scale collaborative processing, and channel estimation, which are related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also discusses radio resource allocation and optimization, which is related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. The paper also discusses the involvement of edge cache, big data mining, and cognitive radio, which are related to augmented reality and human-computer interaction, making cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Human-Computer Interaction) another possible category. Finally, the paper also discusses the progress of testbed development and trial test, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category.
